<div class="page-intro">
  <p class="page-intro__description">
    When it comes to milk, consider offering more than one kind of milk 
    since a lot of people are either intolerant or allergic to a certain kind of milk.  
    Make sure you test your teas with different kinds of milk to ensure flavor consistency. 
    Here are some options to consider beside regular cow's milk.
  </p>
</div>


<ul class="terminal-list">
  <li class="terminal-list__item">
    <h2 class="terminal-list__title">Lactose Free Milk</h2>
    <p class="terminal-list__description"> 
      People with lactose-intolerance are unable to digest the lactose (sugar) 
      in regular cowâ€™s milk. As a results, they may experience potentially upsetting gastrointestinal symptoms.  
      We recommend using lactose-free milk as your main milk base  since it has a longer shelf-life 
      and naturally tastes sweeter so you can save on sweetener.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li class="terminal-list__item">
    <h2 class="terminal-list__title">Soy Milk</h2>
    <p class="terminal-list__description"> 
      Soy milk has a longer shelf-life than regular milk and is usually 
      made from whole soybeans or full-fat soy flour. 
    </p>
  </li>
  <li class="terminal-list__item">
    <h2 class="terminal-list__title">Almond Milk</h2>
    <p class="terminal-list__description"> 
      With it's creamy texture and nutty taste, almond milk has gained popularity, 
      plus it contains neither cholesterol nor lactose and has a longer shelf life. 
    </p>
  </li>
  <li class="terminal-list__item">
    <h2 class="terminal-list__title">Coconut Milk</h2>
    <p class="terminal-list__description"> 
      Coconut milk is another dairy-free option with a long shelf-life. 
      Originally more popular in Southeast Asia and the Carribean, 
      coconut milk has been an increasing choice for many Bubble Tea or Coffee shops.
    </p>
  </li>
  <li class="terminal-list__item">
    <h2 class="terminal-list__title">Condensed Milk</h2>
    <p class="terminal-list__description"> 
      Sweetened condensed milk is the key ingredient for many of the drink flavors such as 
      Thai Tea and Vietnamese coffee. It has thick and creamy consistency and also serves as a sweetener. 
    </p>
  </li>
</ul>
